Seven persons have reportedly been killed in a ghastly motor accident along Abuja- Lokoja road in Kogi State. The incident happened at Akpanya near Koton Karfe on Abuja-Lokoja road between a Toyota Hiace bus and DAF Articulated Vehicle. DAILY POST gathered that the incident occurred around 4.40 am on Thursday. The incident which saw five others injured was caused by a head-on collision between the two vehicles. The Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps, (FRSC), Stephen Dawulung confirmed the incident to DAILY POST on Thursday evening. Dawulung further stated that the accident was caused by speed and route violation by either of the affected vehicles. â€œAlready the injured were rushed to Koton Karfe Hospital, where they are being treated by medical personnel while the seven corpses have been deposited at the morgue he said. The Sector Commander warned drivers to desist from night journeys, stressing that, many lives have been lost as a result of overspeeding.